      • parseNextFieldValue

        boolean parseNextFieldValue​(JsonParsingContext parsingContext)
                     throws BindingException,
                            java.io.IOException
        Parses the next value.

        When called, the current token is expected to be at the value which may be a JsonToken.START_ARRAY for an array of values, a JsonToken.START_OBJECT for a single object, or one of the JsonToken value types.

        After this call completes the parser's current token is expected either at the start of the next value or at the end of the value sequence.

        If at the start of the next value, the current token will be a JsonToken.START_OBJECT for the next object in an array, or one of the JsonToken value types.

        Once the end of the value sequence is reached and all values have been parsed, the current token is expected to be at the JsonToken.END_ARRAY if the inside an array, or otherwise the JsonToken.END_OBJECT for this object.

        Parameters:
        parsingContext - the collection of objects used for parsing
        Returns:
        true if there are additional fields to parse, meaning that the end of the value sequence has not been seen, or false otherwise.
        Throws:
        BindingException - if a binding error has occurred
        java.io.IOException - if an input error has occurred while parsing
